<TITLE> Fog halts ferries for 9 hours </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Munshiganj, Jan 18 (bdnews24.com)Dense fog forced ferry operations on the Maowa-Keorakandi riverway to remained closed for nine hours on Monday. Four ferries were stuck up in the Padma from 2am on Sunday to 11 a.m on Monday, creating a long jam at Maowa and Kaorakandi piers. BIWTC Maowa Ghat manager Serajul Islam told journalists that light was not visible on the channel due to heavy fog, forcing suspension of ferry movement. Ro Ro ferries Shah Makhdum, Raniganj, Roypura and Taplu were compelled to anchor at mid-Padma. Karnaphuly, Jessore and Thobal at Maowa pier and Ro Ro ferries Bhasha Shaheed Barkat, Jamuna, Lenting , Karabi and Ranikhet anchored at Keorakandhi pier. A BIWTC. official said about 500 vehicles were stranded on both the piers on the Dhaka-Khulna highway. The jam eased after the ferry movement resumed. bdn
